===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈɛd.ɪ.bəl/}} {{SAMPA|/"Ed.I.b@l/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# That can be [[eat]]en without harm; non-[[toxic]] to [[human]]s; suitable for [[consumption]].
#: '''''edible''' [[fruit]]''
# That can be eaten without [[disgust]].
#: ''Although stale, the bread was '''edible'''.''

====Usage notes====
'''edible''' is the most common term for “capable of being eaten”; {{term|eatable|lang=en}} is rather informal, due to simple analysis as {{term|eat|lang=en}} + {{term|-able|lang=en}}, while {{term|comestible|lang=en}} is relatively formal.

